{"task_id": "maximum-size-subarray-sum-equals-k", "question_id": 325, "difficulty": "Medium", "tags": ["Array", "Hash Table", "Prefix Sum"], "problem_description": "Given an integer array nums and an integer k, return the maximum length of a subarray that sums to k. If there is not one, return 0 instead.\n \nExample 1:\n\nInput: nums = [1,-1,5,-2,3], k = 3\nOutput: 4\nExplanation: The subarray [1, -1, 5, -2] sums to 3 and is the longest.\n\nExample 2:\n\nInput: nums = [-2,-1,2,1], k = 1\nOutput: 2\nExplanation: The subarray [-1, 2] sums to 1 and is the longest.\n\n \nConstraints:\n\n1 <= nums.length <= 2 * 105\n-104 <= nums[i] <= 104\n-109 <= k <= 109\n\n", "starter_code": "class Solution:\n    def maxSubArrayLen(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:\n        ", "completion": "class Solution:\n    def maxSubArrayLen(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:\n        d = {0: -1}\n        ans = s = 0\n        for i, x in enumerate(nums):\n            s += x\n            if s - k in d:\n                ans = max(ans, i - d[s - k])\n            if s not in d:\n                d[s] = i\n        return ans\n", "entry_point": "Solution().maxSubArrayLen", "test": "def check(candidate):\n    assert candidate(nums = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5],k = 100) == 0\n    assert candidate(nums = [5, 5, 5, 5, 5],k = 10) == 2\n    assert candidate(nums = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5],k = 9) == 3\n    assert candidate(nums = [0, 0, 0, 0, 0],k = 0) == 5\n    assert candidate(nums = [-1, -2, -3, -4, -5],k = 0) == 0\n    assert candidate(nums = [0, 0, 0, 0, 0],k = 1) == 0\n    assert candidate(nums = [10000, -10000, 10000, -10000, 10000],k = 0) == 4\n    assert candidate(nums = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5],k = 20) == 0\n    assert candidate(nums = [-1, -2, -3, -4, -5],k = -15) == 5\n    assert candidate(nums = [-1, -2, -3, -4, -5],k = -9) == 3\n    assert candidate(nums = [10, 20, 30, 40, 50],k = 100) == 4\n    assert candidate(nums = [10, -10, 10, -10, 10],k = 0) == 4\n    assert candidate(nums = [1, -1, 5, -2, 3],k = 3) == 4\n   